title: GD Manica
text:
Grupo Desportivo de Manica is a traditional <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a> club based in <a href="Manica%20Province">Manica Province</a>, <a href="Mozambique">Mozambique</a>, which currently competes in the Moçambola 2 and Manica Provincial League. The club was founded in 1980. Desportivo Manica reached the Interprovincial Stage of the <a href="Ta%C3%A7a%20de%20Mo%C3%A7ambique">Taça de Moçambique</a> in 2009. Desportivo Manica won three consecutive Manica Provincial League championships from 2006 to 2008.
Stadium.
The club plays their home matches at FutEco Park located in <a href="Manica%2C%20Mozambique">Manica</a>, which was funded with a grant from FIFA.
